From Tony John, Port Harcourt Unknown gunmen have kidnapped the monarch of Ikuru town in Andoni Local Government Area of Rivers State, His Royal Majesty, Aaron Ikuru. Daily Sun has learned that the traditional ruler was abducted at his residence in Ikuru town at the weekend. A reliable source at the monarch’s palace has confirmed the abduction, saying that the incident occurred about 8:30 pm on Sunday. The source disclosed that the yet-to-be-identified kidnappers whisked the traditional ruler to an unknown destination. He said the bandits have not contacted the victim’s family since the incident and appealed to security agencies to rescue him unhurt. State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) Nnamdi Omoni, a Superintendent of Police (SP), has confirmed the abduction. Omoni  said that the state Police Command has intensified efforts to rescue the victim and apprehend the fleeing suspects. ‘It’s confirmed and all hands are on deck to ensure his release,’ Omoni stated. 